00:05:41.580 --> 00:06:11.560
criteria, which are listed below, they often would be admitted immediately. But the time from CAR-T to admission ended up being a median of 4.8 days. Whereas if they had routine criteria, which then said, you know, come into the clinic, be evaluated, that actually ended up with more quicker admission. I think that's what I got on there. And then what about our community paramedics? So the idea is that

00:06:11.580 --> 00:06:17.840
we know that after day 14 and through day 30, you rarely see significant toxicity,

00:06:18.520 --> 00:06:24.080
but you do often have transfusion needs. And so we can send the community paramedics out to the

00:06:24.080 --> 00:06:29.300
patient where the patient is staying and have blood work taken to assess for transfusion needs.

00:06:29.380 --> 00:06:35.960
They can do a physical exam. And if the patient needs, they will be sent into the outpatient unit.

00:06:36.380 --> 00:06:40.320
We did look at patients who are enrolled in the community

00:06:40.320 --> 00:06:47.080
paramedic program versus those who came in in the standard day 14 through 30 in the outpatient unit.

00:06:47.540 --> 00:06:56.040
As you can see, there really wasn't, it triggered CRS in one patient out of the 21 in the community

00:06:56.040 --> 00:07:03.340
paramedic program. So it does provide a benefit that you probably don't need all of the visits

00:07:03.340 --> 00:07:10.160
into the clinic. Additionally, we weren't seeing an increased number of infections,

00:07:10.320 --> 00:07:15.580
and these patients, you know, when the patients were admitted, it was a similar duration of stay

00:07:15.580 --> 00:07:22.620
as in those patients that came through with no community paramedic. So key takeaways. So

00:07:22.620 --> 00:07:29.820
an outpatient CAR-T hospital-based outpatient program is feasible. It's safe. It's probably

00:07:29.820 --> 00:07:35.100
more cost effective. With the remote patient monitoring, you get additional data points that

00:07:35.100 --> 00:07:40.300
may trigger a visit or an admission. And then finally, by incorporating a community paramedic,

00:07:40.320 --> 00:07:46.660
you can reduce the clinical burden, all of the visits, the cost, and it is reimbursable.

00:07:46.660 --> 00:07:48.320
So with that, I'd say thank you.
